NOTE /SegmentIndex

                                                                                                                                                                                            


1
00:00:09.276 --> 00:00:11.764 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[muffled shouting]

2
00:00:11.797 --> 00:00:13.238 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Look, save your energy.

3
00:00:13.378 --> 00:00:15.537 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We'll have you out of there
as soon as possible.

4
00:00:18.167 --> 00:00:18.936 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I hope.

5
00:00:21.713 --> 00:00:23.374 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Try rerouting
the power coupling.

6
00:00:27.672 --> 00:00:29.271 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mr. O'Brien.

7
00:00:29.352 --> 00:00:31.551 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
See if you can activate
the interlock servos.

8
00:00:31.631 --> 00:00:33.030 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mr. O'Brien.

9
00:00:33.030 --> 00:00:36.742 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain Jaheel, those people
have been stuck in that air lock

10
00:00:36.742 --> 00:00:37.566 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
for over an hour.

11
00:00:37.929 --> 00:00:39.930 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, if you can wait
till we get that door opened

12
00:00:39.930 --> 00:00:42.210 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll be happy to listen
to any problems you might have.

13
00:00:42.348 --> 00:00:45.270 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But I've already been waiting two days
for your people to readjust

14
00:00:45.270 --> 00:00:47.030 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
my ship's antimatter flow converter.

15
00:00:47.546 --> 00:00:50.248 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm afraid we've gotten a little behind
in our maintenance schedule.

16
00:00:50.425 --> 00:00:52.006 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm not interested in hearing excuses.

17
00:00:52.006 --> 00:00:55.117 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I have a shipment of Tamen Sahsheer
waiting to be delivered to Largo V,

18
00:00:55.244 --> 00:00:58.206 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and I'll need to do better than warp 1
to get there before it spoils.

19
00:00:58.403 --> 00:01:01.785 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll try to get a repair crew
to you by the end of the day.

20
00:01:02.101 --> 00:01:03.242 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now, that's the best I can do.

21
00:01:03.501 --> 00:01:05.983 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your best, Mr. O'Brien,
hardly seems good enough.

22
00:01:09.579 --> 00:01:11.139 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[woman]<i> Dax to O'Brien.</i>

23
00:01:11.218 --> 00:01:12.758 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
O'Brien here.

24
00:01:12.778 --> 00:01:13.938 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Can you spare a minute, Chief?</i>

25
00:01:14.018 --> 00:01:15.768 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I have a little problem here at the lab.</i>

26
00:01:18.160 --> 00:01:19.336 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
On my way.

27
00:01:24.895 --> 00:01:26.214 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thanks for coming, Chief.

28
00:01:26.294 --> 00:01:28.014 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What are you doing out here?

29
00:01:30.373 --> 00:01:32.092 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[loud whining]

30
00:01:35.132 --> 00:01:37.091 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Have you checked the EPS converter?

31
00:01:37.171 --> 00:01:39.099 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, first thing.

32
00:01:38.731 --> 00:01:41.010 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-How about the intensity grid?
-It's fine.

33
00:01:41.090 --> 00:01:43.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Then it's probably the secondary
phase modulator.

34
00:01:43.849 --> 00:01:46.888 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We had trouble with them last week
in the main power core.

35
00:01:49.168 --> 00:01:50.746 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That should do it.

36
00:01:50.767 --> 00:01:52.460 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[noise stops]

37
00:01:56.047 --> 00:01:57.445 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Anything else I can do for you?

38
00:01:59.834 --> 00:02:02.656 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The navigational computer
hasn't worked reliably for three days.

39
00:02:03.103 --> 00:02:05.364 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I ask for the star charts
for the Argosian sector--

40
00:02:06.053 --> 00:02:07.643 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Glessene sector
comes up instead.

41
00:02:08.162 --> 00:02:10.343 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's when I can coax
this system on line.

42
00:02:10.801 --> 00:02:12.080 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[O'Brien] Uh-huh.

43
00:02:12.161 --> 00:02:13.880 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Try it now.

44
00:02:15.799 --> 00:02:18.279 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh! That's more like it.

45
00:02:27.796 --> 00:02:29.197 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You look like you
could use some sleep.

46
00:02:30.028 --> 00:02:31.077 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Who has time for sleep?

47
00:02:32.306 --> 00:02:35.145 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'd settle for five minutes
peace and quiet.

48
00:02:38.724 --> 00:02:40.635 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Chief, I thought you were going
to fix the replicators.

49
00:02:42.331 --> 00:02:44.252 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're absolutely right, sir.

50
00:02:44.252 --> 00:02:45.632 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I knew I'd forgotten something.

51
00:02:46.010 --> 00:02:48.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Can't have the Operations Chief
sitting around daydreaming

52
00:02:48.812 --> 00:02:50.492 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
when there's work
to be done, can we?

53
00:02:50.811 --> 00:02:53.130 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Ho, ho, ho, ho.
I'll get right on it.

54
00:02:53.130 --> 00:02:51.408 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"Fix the replicators, Chief."

55
00:02:55.489 --> 00:02:57.427 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"My console's off-line, Chief."

56
00:02:57.448 --> 00:02:58.808 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groaning]

57
00:03:00.188 --> 00:03:02.627 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I should have transferred
to a cargo drone--

58
00:03:03.725 --> 00:03:05.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
no people, no complaints.

59
00:03:26.938 --> 00:03:28.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

60
00:03:35.976 --> 00:03:37.575 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[instrument humming]

61
00:03:44.013 --> 00:03:46.601 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hot coffee-- black, double sweet.

62
00:04:15.963 --> 00:04:17.963 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[beeping]

63
00:06:10.649 --> 00:06:12.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Odo] Tell me, Quark.

64
00:06:12.949 --> 00:06:16.892 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Am I mistaken, or is business
a little slow today?

65
00:06:17.367 --> 00:06:21.426 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Slow? It's been almost nonexistent
for the past three days.

66
00:06:21.446 --> 00:06:23.446 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Mmm. Who knows?

67
00:06:24.145 --> 00:06:27.467 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
If things don't improve
you may be forced to close down.

68
00:06:27.904 --> 00:06:29.464 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Oh, you'd like that, wouldn't you?

69
00:06:29.563 --> 00:06:34.306 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Well, let's just say, without you around
my job would be considerably easier.

70
00:06:34.522 --> 00:06:37.241 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Without me around,
you'd be forced to find

71
00:06:37.241 --> 00:06:39.232 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
some other poor innocent to persecute.

72
00:06:40.080 --> 00:06:43.983 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Think about that while you sit here
gloating at my misfortune.

73
00:06:44.359 --> 00:06:45.398 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Quark!

74
00:06:45.699 --> 00:06:47.604 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
You call this Kohlian stew?

75
00:06:53.336 --> 00:06:58.299 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
If your meal isn't satisfactory
I'm sure we could, uh, exchange it

76
00:06:58.334 --> 00:06:59.815 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
for something more to your liking.

77
00:07:00.315 --> 00:07:04.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Aren't you the least bit curious
as to how it tastes?

78
00:07:07.352 --> 00:07:09.792 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[groaning]

79
00:07:10.511 --> 00:07:11.111 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Now...

80
00:07:11.111 --> 00:07:11.852 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
you served it.

81
00:07:12.251 --> 00:07:13.212 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're going to eat it.

82
00:07:14.240 --> 00:07:15.690 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right, that's enough.

83
00:07:16.827 --> 00:07:17.929 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I said, eat it!

84
00:07:19.809 --> 00:07:21.248 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I said...

85
00:07:21.848 --> 00:07:23.287 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
that's enough.

86
00:07:24.028 --> 00:07:24.929 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Leave him alone.

87
00:07:29.945 --> 00:07:33.465 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Well, another satisfied customer.

88
00:07:35.304 --> 00:07:37.343 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's these replicators.

89
00:07:37.343 --> 00:07:39.714 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If I don't get them fixed soon,
they'll destroy my business.

90
00:07:40.062 --> 00:07:41.643 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why not get O'Brien to fix them?

91
00:07:41.881 --> 00:07:44.603 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He has the replicators on
the command level working perfectly.

92
00:07:45.113 --> 00:07:46.762 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm on his waiting list.

93
00:07:47.480 --> 00:07:50.142 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He assures me he'll get to them
as soon as he can.

94
00:07:50.885 --> 00:07:51.959 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mmm...

95
00:07:52.039 --> 00:07:54.680 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No telling when that will be.

96
00:07:54.680 --> 00:07:56.111 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The Chief's a very busy man.

97
00:08:01.216 --> 00:08:01.856 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Computer...

98
00:08:03.495 --> 00:08:05.134 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
display a station layout.

99
00:08:07.074 --> 00:08:10.433 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Highlight locations
of all repaired replicators

100
00:08:10.433 --> 00:08:11.274 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
on command level.

101
00:08:11.933 --> 00:08:13.094 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female voice on machine]
<i>Information restricted</i>

102
00:08:13.094 --> 00:08:15.224 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>to security clearance 5 and above.</i>

103
00:08:15.472 --> 00:08:17.313 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Please enter security verification.</i>

104
00:08:33.066 --> 00:08:34.866 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Clearance verified.</i>

105
00:08:47.356 --> 00:08:47.782 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There you go, sir.

106
00:08:48.202 --> 00:08:50.103 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think you'll find that
more to your liking.

107
00:08:51.061 --> 00:08:52.682 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Very much appreciated, Mr. O'Brien.

108
00:08:53.261 --> 00:08:54.260 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don't mention it, sir.

109
00:08:54.260 --> 00:08:55.600 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Unfortunately,
there are plenty of replicators

110
00:08:55.839 --> 00:08:57.580 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
around the station
that still need looking after.

111
00:08:58.959 --> 00:08:59.840 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You all right, Chief?

112
00:09:01.159 --> 00:09:02.638 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm just a bit hot.

113
00:09:03.058 --> 00:09:05.099 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The environmental controls
must be acting up again.

114
00:09:05.657 --> 00:09:07.057 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Send my regards to Mrs. O'Brien.

115
00:09:07.057 --> 00:09:08.608 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jake tells me she's a wonderful teacher.

116
00:09:08.816 --> 00:09:10.456 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, that's nice to hear, sir.

117
00:09:10.595 --> 00:09:12.216 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She's flower units about the lad herself.

118
00:09:12.314 --> 00:09:12.814 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Excuse me?

119
00:09:14.454 --> 00:09:14.714 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sir?

120
00:09:14.714 --> 00:09:15.684 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What was that you just said?

121
00:09:17.413 --> 00:09:20.395 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She's... quite fond of the lad herself.

122
00:09:21.692 --> 00:09:22.891 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh.

123
00:09:23.613 --> 00:09:24.491 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm glad to hear it.

124
00:09:24.571 --> 00:09:26.603 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Very good, sir.

125
00:09:33.689 --> 00:09:35.168 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[man] Ladies.

126
00:09:35.248 --> 00:09:36.728 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hello, Lieutenant.

127
00:09:37.688 --> 00:09:40.206 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, I forgot how different it was.

128
00:09:40.287 --> 00:09:41.846 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How different what was?

129
00:09:42.126 --> 00:09:43.686 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Being female.

130
00:09:43.765 --> 00:09:45.644 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I haven't been one for over 80 years.

131
00:09:46.344 --> 00:09:47.265 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All this attention.

132
00:09:47.265 --> 00:09:48.955 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Imagine it must take
some getting used to.

133
00:09:49.083 --> 00:09:50.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Actually, I find it quite enjoyable.

134
00:09:50.763 --> 00:09:52.082 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Major Kira.

135
00:09:52.163 --> 00:09:53.602 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Lieutenant Dax.

136
00:09:54.523 --> 00:09:57.505 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'd be honored to have you
join my little party--

137
00:09:57.505 --> 00:09:58.654 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
as my guests, of course.

138
00:09:59.065 --> 00:10:00.584 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's all this, Quark?

139
00:10:00.664 --> 00:10:02.824 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You cheat your 1,000th customer?

140
00:10:03.240 --> 00:10:05.442 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Who says Bajorans
don't have a sense of humor?

141
00:10:06.179 --> 00:10:10.882 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Actually, uh, we're celebrating the repair
of the bar's replicator system.

142
00:10:11.337 --> 00:10:13.819 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Perhaps I could interest you

143
00:10:14.016 --> 00:10:17.679 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
in a nice, double-whipped,
I'danian spice pudding.

144
00:10:17.846 --> 00:10:19.016 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, what do you think?

145
00:10:19.925 --> 00:10:21.506 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think I'm due back at Ops

146
00:10:21.714 --> 00:10:23.074 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but, uh, go on.

147
00:10:23.074 --> 00:10:23.814 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Enjoy yourself.

148
00:10:36.151 --> 00:10:37.310 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Chief?

149
00:10:37.910 --> 00:10:39.390 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[slurring] How can I help you, Major?

150
00:10:41.353 --> 00:10:43.529 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Looks like you're the one
who could use a little help.

151
00:10:44.112 --> 00:10:45.992 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, no, I'm fine, really.

152
00:10:50.486 --> 00:10:52.407 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I suppose this isn't
a good time to tell you

153
00:10:52.407 --> 00:10:54.558 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that number three turbolift
has broken down again.

154
00:10:58.845 --> 00:11:00.525 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Joking, Chief.

155
00:11:02.282 --> 00:11:03.781 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Major, lark's true pepper.

156
00:11:05.081 --> 00:11:06.201 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What?

157
00:11:08.800 --> 00:11:10.461 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let birds go further loose maybe.

158
00:11:12.718 --> 00:11:13.759 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Shout easy play.

159
00:11:13.759 --> 00:11:16.678 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Chief, you're not making any sense.

160
00:11:16.838 --> 00:11:18.119 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Round the turbulent quick.

161
00:11:22.755 --> 00:11:24.656 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, close the reverse harbor.

162
00:11:28.754 --> 00:11:31.176 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A-Ankle try sound.

163
00:11:32.453 --> 00:11:33.294 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Reset gleaming.

164
00:11:35.923 --> 00:11:36.913 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
D-Dinner to bug.

165
00:11:40.322 --> 00:11:42.341 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Chief, wait.

166
00:11:42.361 --> 00:11:43.560 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
When?

167
00:11:43.641 --> 00:11:44.680 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Chief.

168
00:11:57.197 --> 00:12:00.356 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Computer, continue neural imaging scan

169
00:12:00.424 --> 00:12:01.685 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and stimulate visual cortex.

170
00:12:02.424 --> 00:12:04.165 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female automated voice]
<i>All visual responses normal.</i>

171
00:12:09.702 --> 00:12:10.863 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Begin auditory stimuli.

172
00:12:11.641 --> 00:12:13.242 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[woman]<i> No physiological damage.</i>

173
00:12:13.560 --> 00:12:16.160 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>All brain functions</i>
<i>within normal parameters.</i>

174
00:12:17.999 --> 00:12:19.558 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Nurse.
-Yes?

175
00:12:20.319 --> 00:12:23.391 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Will you pull up Mr. O'Brien's
neurophysiological history, please?

176
00:12:22.957 --> 00:12:23.988 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, Doctor.

177
00:12:31.995 --> 00:12:33.596 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What is that? What's he written?

178
00:12:33.762 --> 00:12:34.963 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I wish I knew.

179
00:12:35.233 --> 00:12:38.431 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Strike limits flame the dark true salt.

180
00:12:38.512 --> 00:12:39.752 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Please, Chief, take a seat.

181
00:12:39.936 --> 00:12:41.471 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Way link complete.

182
00:12:41.551 --> 00:12:42.990 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Way link!

183
00:12:47.250 --> 00:12:48.231 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's wrong with him?

184
00:12:48.490 --> 00:12:50.571 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He appears to suffering
from a form of aphasia.

185
00:12:51.109 --> 00:12:52.370 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's a perceptual dysfunction

186
00:12:52.370 --> 00:12:55.271 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
in which aural and visual stimuli
are incorrectly processed by the brain.

187
00:12:55.828 --> 00:12:57.349 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
His actual thinking hasn't been affected

188
00:12:58.267 --> 00:12:59.808 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but he's incapable of expressing himself

189
00:12:59.947 --> 00:13:02.370 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
or understanding others.

190
00:13:02.426 --> 00:13:05.505 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Victory strike limits frosted wake.

191
00:13:06.984 --> 00:13:09.344 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Simple hesitation!

192
00:13:10.064 --> 00:13:11.703 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm not sure I follow you, Doctor.

193
00:13:11.783 --> 00:13:13.182 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You say Mr. O'Brien is aphasiac

194
00:13:13.182 --> 00:13:14.724 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but all of his tests
have come up negative.

195
00:13:16.361 --> 00:13:19.683 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Isn't aphasia typically associated
with some kind of cranial trauma?

196
00:13:20.380 --> 00:13:23.242 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yes. It can occur as a result of a stroke
or a blow to the head.

197
00:13:23.700 --> 00:13:24.901 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But there's no evidence of that here.

198
00:13:25.179 --> 00:13:27.441 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Did you check the medical library
for any precedents?

199
00:13:27.498 --> 00:13:29.619 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And rechecked-- nothing, so far.

200
00:13:30.378 --> 00:13:31.559 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You have any theories?

201
00:13:32.817 --> 00:13:33.378 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not yet.

202
00:13:34.136 --> 00:13:35.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Find one.

203
00:13:35.416 --> 00:13:37.998 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Major Kira, get a hold
of the Chief's personal duty log.

204
00:13:37.998 --> 00:13:40.673 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I want to know where he's been
and what he's done for the past 52 hours.

205
00:13:40.673 --> 00:13:43.986 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've already examined it, Commander.
He's been all over this station.

206
00:13:43.993 --> 00:13:46.054 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Retrace his steps and see what
you come up with.

207
00:13:46.812 --> 00:13:49.674 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Dax, you will temporarily assume
Mr. O'Brien's duties.

208
00:13:50.331 --> 00:13:52.131 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, uh... Um...

209
00:13:52.211 --> 00:13:53.970 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Is there a problem, Lieutenant?

210
00:13:55.090 --> 00:13:56.570 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Lieutenant?

211
00:13:57.850 --> 00:14:00.648 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm sorry, Benjamin.

212
00:14:00.949 --> 00:14:01.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm unable to...

213
00:14:03.928 --> 00:14:05.949 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
foolish assembled regal...

214
00:14:07.006 --> 00:14:08.686 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
control weather.

215
00:14:19.182 --> 00:14:22.564 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Spontaneous development of aphasia
is virtually impossible.

216
00:14:23.122 --> 00:14:26.244 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yet we saw Lieutenant Dax
become aphasiac before our eyes.

217
00:14:26.461 --> 00:14:27.882 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This told me we were
dealing with a disease

218
00:14:27.882 --> 00:14:29.092 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
which only mimics aphasia,

219
00:14:30.899 --> 00:14:33.761 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so I ran a full neural synaptic comparison
between Dax and O'Brien

220
00:14:34.138 --> 00:14:36.280 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and I found this in the temporal lobes
of both patients.

221
00:14:36.737 --> 00:14:37.817 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A virus.

222
00:14:37.946 --> 00:14:40.767 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It imposes itself
within the established synaptic pathways

223
00:14:40.767 --> 00:14:42.093 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and then randomly reroutes them.

224
00:14:42.776 --> 00:14:44.818 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
For example, when I look at this,

225
00:14:45.815 --> 00:14:47.316 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
a process occurs within my brain

226
00:14:47.654 --> 00:14:49.423 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
which connects the stimulus
to the word "tricorder."

227
00:14:50.274 --> 00:14:51.975 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This virus disrupts that process.

228
00:14:52.893 --> 00:14:54.213 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'd see a tricorder

229
00:14:54.512 --> 00:14:56.894 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I'd say something ridiculous,
like "window."

230
00:14:57.272 --> 00:14:58.431 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Exactly.

231
00:14:58.511 --> 00:14:59.991 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Doctor, I think you should get over here.

232
00:15:00.070 --> 00:15:01.950 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Night the flow trade again.
-You lost pile luck.

233
00:15:01.950 --> 00:15:03.831 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Away tunnel back the garden.

234
00:15:03.949 --> 00:15:06.577 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Doctor, I want this station

235
00:15:06.577 --> 00:15:08.152 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
put under emergency quarantine
immediately.

236
00:15:07.861 --> 00:15:08.941 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, sir.

237
00:15:13.259 --> 00:15:16.059 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[conversation and music]

238
00:15:16.138 --> 00:15:17.219 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[man] Dabo!

239
00:15:17.298 --> 00:15:18.338 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[shouting]

240
00:15:24.376 --> 00:15:28.615 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Quark, what is going on here?

241
00:15:29.976 --> 00:15:31.218 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What does it look like?

242
00:15:31.218 --> 00:15:32.811 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It looks like business as usual

243
00:15:32.811 --> 00:15:33.787 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but that's impossible

244
00:15:33.787 --> 00:15:37.446 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
because all shops and businesses
have been closed until further notice.

245
00:15:37.446 --> 00:15:40.414 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Except, of course,
for essential station operations.

246
00:15:40.366 --> 00:15:42.764 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
For which this place hardly qualifies.

247
00:15:42.764 --> 00:15:43.771 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't think they'd agree.

248
00:15:44.357 --> 00:15:46.899 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This quarantine has everybody
on edge, Constable.

249
00:15:47.316 --> 00:15:49.798 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Would you deprive them
of a little harmless diversion?

250
00:15:54.674 --> 00:15:57.553 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They'd be safer in their quarters.

251
00:15:57.914 --> 00:16:01.432 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Quark, this Kohlian stew-- magnificent.

252
00:16:02.032 --> 00:16:04.522 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Fortunately, my assistant, Rom,
was able to fix the replicators.

253
00:16:07.671 --> 00:16:11.589 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes... Very fortunate.

254
00:16:28.704 --> 00:16:29.903 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Sisko] Jake...

255
00:16:29.984 --> 00:16:31.623 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I expected you home an hour ago.

256
00:16:31.703 --> 00:16:33.342 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sorry. I was at Nog's.

257
00:16:33.863 --> 00:16:35.462 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dad, about this quarantine--

258
00:16:35.542 --> 00:16:36.901 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
it's going to be OK, isn't it?

259
00:16:36.901 --> 00:16:38.263 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's just a precaution, nothing more.

260
00:16:38.421 --> 00:16:40.062 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Jaheel] I wish I shared your
confidence, Commander.

261
00:16:41.440 --> 00:16:42.441 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Go straight home, son.

262
00:16:43.456 --> 00:16:44.479 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll see you at dinner.

263
00:16:45.719 --> 00:16:48.601 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain Jaheel, all visitors
have been confined to their ships.

264
00:16:48.698 --> 00:16:50.659 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Believe me,
there is no place I'd rather be.

265
00:16:51.255 --> 00:16:51.906 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then what are you doing here?

266
00:16:52.576 --> 00:16:55.678 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Commander, I officially request permission
to leave this station.

267
00:16:55.793 --> 00:16:56.694 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Request denied.

268
00:16:56.694 --> 00:16:59.442 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But none of my crew
has been affected by this virus of yours.

269
00:16:59.474 --> 00:17:02.956 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And unless I depart at once
my whole cargo will be ruined!

270
00:17:03.074 --> 00:17:06.917 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain, I suggest
you return to your ship now.

271
00:17:08.352 --> 00:17:12.431 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Please. I don't want to get sick.

272
00:17:13.391 --> 00:17:17.034 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm sorry, but until we can
find a cure for this... thing,

273
00:17:17.649 --> 00:17:18.610 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
no one's going anywhere.

274
00:17:40.423 --> 00:17:41.144 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Computer,

275
00:17:42.602 --> 00:17:47.285 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
let's start with one
Ferengi Starduster, please.

276
00:17:47.285 --> 00:17:48.383 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Extra strong.

277
00:17:56.602 --> 00:17:57.762 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Perfect.

278
00:18:02.521 --> 00:18:06.080 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Uh... I thought the front wheels
were sticking a bit.

279
00:18:06.215 --> 00:18:09.878 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Unauthorized access
to crew quarters is a crime, Quark.

280
00:18:10.533 --> 00:18:13.023 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You could have just asked
to use the replicators.

281
00:18:14.075 --> 00:18:16.954 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There's an old Ferengi saying--
"Never ask when you can take."

282
00:18:18.474 --> 00:18:20.594 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uh, how did you figure it out?

283
00:18:20.871 --> 00:18:23.031 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You claimed Rom fixed your replicators.

284
00:18:23.589 --> 00:18:25.170 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-So?
-Rom's an idiot.

285
00:18:25.349 --> 00:18:27.490 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He couldn't fix a straw if it was bent.

286
00:18:28.068 --> 00:18:30.308 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're right. Rom is an idiot.

287
00:18:31.467 --> 00:18:34.058 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Remind me to get rid of him tomorrow.

288
00:18:36.806 --> 00:18:39.168 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Based on the levels of the virus
found in the patients' blood,

289
00:18:39.625 --> 00:18:41.286 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I believe it's being
absorbed through ingestion.

290
00:18:41.604 --> 00:18:43.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-You're saying it's in our food?
-Well, that's not possible.

291
00:18:43.804 --> 00:18:47.602 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
All the food on this station is replicated
and all the replicators use biofilters.

292
00:18:47.602 --> 00:18:50.674 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They automatically screen out contaminants
including viruses.

293
00:18:50.674 --> 00:18:53.830 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Major, I've analyzed samples
from replicators all over the station.

294
00:18:54.780 --> 00:18:56.521 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Food on the command level is contaminated.

295
00:18:56.739 --> 00:18:58.389 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But all of us here have
eaten from those replicators.

296
00:18:58.968 --> 00:18:59.639 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How come we're not aphasic?

297
00:18:59.998 --> 00:19:01.939 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This virus is highly adaptable.

298
00:19:02.158 --> 00:19:04.840 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Its incubation period
seems to vary within each individual.

299
00:19:05.557 --> 00:19:07.158 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
According to O'Brien's duty log

300
00:19:07.837 --> 00:19:09.819 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the last thing he did
before becoming aphasic

301
00:19:09.819 --> 00:19:10.972 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
was fix the command level replicators.

302
00:19:12.130 --> 00:19:14.251 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Get a repair crew over there
to inspect the site.

303
00:19:15.134 --> 00:19:16.394 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let's shut down those replicators.

304
00:19:17.114 --> 00:19:19.035 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe we'll be able
to limit further contamination.

305
00:19:19.273 --> 00:19:21.392 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm afraid that's not going to do it, sir.

306
00:19:21.872 --> 00:19:23.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've been getting aphasic patients
from all over the station.

307
00:19:24.092 --> 00:19:24.973 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How is that possible?

308
00:19:25.271 --> 00:19:26.252 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You can thank Quark.

309
00:19:26.490 --> 00:19:29.172 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I caught him using a replicator
in one of the vacant crew quarters.

310
00:19:29.769 --> 00:19:31.931 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He was producing
his entire menu out of there.

311
00:19:34.118 --> 00:19:35.879 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If this virus is present

312
00:19:36.788 --> 00:19:38.890 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
within a large enough segment
of the population

313
00:19:40.085 --> 00:19:40.905 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
it could mean...

314
00:19:42.305 --> 00:19:43.825 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What is it, Doctor?

315
00:19:45.605 --> 00:19:46.726 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I just took an air sample.

316
00:19:49.605 --> 00:19:50.305 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Sisko] The virus...

317
00:19:50.933 --> 00:19:52.322 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's mutated into an airborne variety.

318
00:19:52.342 --> 00:19:53.706 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Which means?

319
00:19:53.742 --> 00:19:57.021 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Which means the whole station is infected.

320
00:20:05.899 --> 00:20:09.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Sisko]<i> Station Log, Stardate 46423.7.</i>

321
00:20:09.998 --> 00:20:13.741 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Nearly 60% of DS9's population</i>
<i>has now contracted the aphasia virus.</i>

322
00:20:14.116 --> 00:20:16.338 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We've initiated standard</i>
<i>quarantine procedures</i>

323
00:20:16.556 --> 00:20:18.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>and are advising all incoming ships</i>

324
00:20:18.157 --> 00:20:19.807 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>to maintain their distance</i>
<i>from the station</i>

325
00:20:20.025 --> 00:20:21.306 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>until further notice.</i>

326
00:20:40.909 --> 00:20:44.587 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I found it in the replicator's
pattern generator.

327
00:20:45.267 --> 00:20:48.009 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
O'Brien must have accidentally
triggered it when he repaired the system.

328
00:20:48.286 --> 00:20:52.289 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
According to Bashir, it introduced
an anomalous programming sequence

329
00:20:52.289 --> 00:20:54.238 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
into the materialization subroutine.

330
00:20:54.238 --> 00:20:56.193 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
In effect, it built the virus

331
00:20:56.193 --> 00:20:59.100 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
directly into the replicated food
at a molecular level.

332
00:20:59.633 --> 00:21:02.152 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-So what we have here is sabotage.
-Cardassian sabotage.

333
00:21:02.152 --> 00:21:05.159 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-How can you be sure?
-Has a diboridium core for a power source.

334
00:21:05.181 --> 00:21:06.922 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That is Cardassian technology.

335
00:21:07.501 --> 00:21:09.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[man]<i> Bashir to Sisko.</i>

336
00:21:10.100 --> 00:21:11.379 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sisko here.

337
00:21:11.460 --> 00:21:13.499 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[man]<i> Commander, I think you'd better</i>
<i>get down here to the infirmary</i>

338
00:21:13.499 --> 00:21:14.319 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>as soon as possible.</i>

339
00:21:14.658 --> 00:21:15.198 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
On my way.

340
00:21:21.336 --> 00:21:23.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You wanted to see me, Doctor?

341
00:21:25.455 --> 00:21:26.735 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jake?

342
00:21:27.575 --> 00:21:30.494 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Left... become better...

343
00:21:30.574 --> 00:21:33.412 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
control... entire hope.

344
00:21:37.092 --> 00:21:38.633 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Bashir] We've converted
some empty crew quarters

345
00:21:38.633 --> 00:21:39.533 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
into a hospital ward.

346
00:21:39.713 --> 00:21:40.713 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He'll be well looked after.

347
00:21:40.852 --> 00:21:42.171 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll take him there myself.

348
00:21:43.132 --> 00:21:45.091 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Come on, Jake.
You're going to be all right.

349
00:21:45.249 --> 00:21:48.792 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Commander, when you've got a moment,
I've found something I'd like to show you.

350
00:21:53.887 --> 00:21:55.497 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[people muttering]

351
00:21:55.166 --> 00:21:57.645 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[woman] It'll be all right.
Just lay back.

352
00:21:57.726 --> 00:21:58.845 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[coughing]

353
00:21:58.925 --> 00:22:01.477 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[woman] I know,
but just lay back and relax.

354
00:22:03.403 --> 00:22:06.483 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Quark] Food... dabo... drinks...

355
00:22:06.562 --> 00:22:09.841 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
money... hand... mine... give!

356
00:22:10.363 --> 00:22:13.665 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, Quark, I see even you couldn't
weasel your way clear of this one.

357
00:22:13.861 --> 00:22:16.423 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You underestimate the Ferengi
immune system, Commander.

358
00:22:16.820 --> 00:22:19.382 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm merely here visiting
my less fortunate customers

359
00:22:19.382 --> 00:22:21.082 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to make sure they're
not faking the illness

360
00:22:21.881 --> 00:22:22.581 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to avoid paying their bills.

361
00:22:22.581 --> 00:22:23.920 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No one could be that devious.

362
00:22:24.791 --> 00:22:25.021 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am.

363
00:22:25.791 --> 00:22:28.779 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You... gold... owe... me!

364
00:22:31.459 --> 00:22:33.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[indistinct conversation]

365
00:22:33.618 --> 00:22:36.017 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Quark] I... now... give...

366
00:22:36.657 --> 00:22:37.936 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Up!

367
00:22:40.612 --> 00:22:41.893 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're doing everything possible.

368
00:22:45.326 --> 00:22:46.912 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll be back as soon as I can.

369
00:22:54.508 --> 00:22:56.089 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The virus is synthetic, Commander.

370
00:22:57.069 --> 00:22:58.850 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Its nucleotide sequence is too perfect.

371
00:22:58.947 --> 00:22:59.868 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's clearly not natural.

372
00:23:00.526 --> 00:23:03.048 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You're saying the Cardassians
genetically engineered this thing?

373
00:23:03.165 --> 00:23:04.366 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, that's what I thought at first,

374
00:23:04.486 --> 00:23:06.367 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I've studied Cardassian
genetic engineering.

375
00:23:06.704 --> 00:23:09.224 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They always build distinctive
monoclonial links into their DNA.

376
00:23:09.404 --> 00:23:10.925 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This virus has none of those features.

377
00:23:11.304 --> 00:23:12.285 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right, then who made it?

378
00:23:12.343 --> 00:23:13.644 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, that's what I wanted to find out.

379
00:23:14.102 --> 00:23:16.324 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So I referenced all known
DNA construction techniques

380
00:23:16.324 --> 00:23:17.394 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
in the Federation records

381
00:23:17.621 --> 00:23:19.442 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and this protein series was the key.

382
00:23:20.561 --> 00:23:21.221 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It indicates--

383
00:23:21.641 --> 00:23:23.641 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Doctor! Who created this virus?

384
00:23:23.720 --> 00:23:25.080 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The Bajorans, sir.

385
00:23:25.519 --> 00:23:26.920 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I believe it must have been
a terrorist plot

386
00:23:26.920 --> 00:23:28.740 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to sabotage the Cardassians
while they were here.

387
00:23:34.598 --> 00:23:36.318 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The energy decay of the power core

388
00:23:36.397 --> 00:23:39.557 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
indicates it dates back
to the building of the station.

389
00:23:39.637 --> 00:23:41.596 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Odo] That's 18 years ago.

390
00:23:42.034 --> 00:23:43.455 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I suppose the Bajoran underground

391
00:23:43.455 --> 00:23:45.506 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
could have smuggled it aboard
during construction...

392
00:23:46.168 --> 00:23:48.590 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
before I took over as Head of Security.

393
00:23:49.212 --> 00:23:51.254 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But why would the underground
go to all the trouble

394
00:23:51.254 --> 00:23:53.124 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
of planting a booby trap
and not set it off?

395
00:23:53.531 --> 00:23:54.412 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe they forgot.

396
00:23:54.731 --> 00:23:58.294 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No. More likely, they were captured
or killed before they could release it.

397
00:23:58.889 --> 00:24:01.408 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We need to find out
who created this virus.

398
00:24:01.779 --> 00:24:02.949 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're our best hope.

399
00:24:05.442 --> 00:24:07.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighing] 18 years is a long time.

400
00:24:07.866 --> 00:24:11.709 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Besides, even if she finds who did this,
that's no guarantee they can help us.

401
00:24:12.205 --> 00:24:14.067 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We just have to hope
they remember the antidote.

402
00:24:14.324 --> 00:24:16.586 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's assuming they ever
bothered to create one.

403
00:24:24.961 --> 00:24:26.600 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It had to be someone
in the underground

404
00:24:26.681 --> 00:24:28.259 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
familiar with genetic engineering.

405
00:24:28.280 --> 00:24:29.680 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Galis]<i> Eighteen years ago?</i>

406
00:24:29.960 --> 00:24:31.942 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Sounds like something Dekon Elig</i>
<i>might have thought up.</i>

407
00:24:32.301 --> 00:24:33.200 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How can I find him?

408
00:24:33.639 --> 00:24:35.781 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The last I heard</i>
<i>he was in a Cardassian prison.</i>

409
00:24:36.329 --> 00:24:37.218 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where was he being held?

410
00:24:37.238 --> 00:24:39.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>The Velos VII Internment Camp,</i>

411
00:24:39.457 --> 00:24:41.979 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>but that was nine years ago.</i>

412
00:24:44.535 --> 00:24:46.775 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And you have no idea where he is now?

413
00:24:47.319 --> 00:24:48.920 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Think, Galis! This is important.

414
00:24:49.414 --> 00:24:52.997 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I'm sorry, Kira,</i>
<i>but it was all so long ago.</i>

415
00:24:58.971 --> 00:25:00.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What is it, Jake?

416
00:25:00.331 --> 00:25:02.170 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Roll linger when life.

417
00:25:02.250 --> 00:25:03.610 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Roll linger when...

418
00:25:03.689 --> 00:25:04.969 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What?

419
00:25:11.928 --> 00:25:14.309 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Other support, strong courage...

420
00:25:16.567 --> 00:25:18.207 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasps]

421
00:25:19.904 --> 00:25:21.085 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's running a high fever.

422
00:25:21.984 --> 00:25:23.304 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Open way long.

423
00:25:23.384 --> 00:25:24.384 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Open way.

424
00:25:27.503 --> 00:25:29.622 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Doctor, we have an emergency
in crew quarters.

425
00:25:44.252 --> 00:25:45.337 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How is he, Doctor?

426
00:25:45.397 --> 00:25:46.418 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not good, I'm afraid.

427
00:25:47.196 --> 00:25:49.278 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The virus has attacked
his autonomic nervous system.

428
00:25:49.416 --> 00:25:50.537 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Can he be stabilized?

429
00:25:50.936 --> 00:25:52.737 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He hasn't responded to neural stimulation.

430
00:25:53.355 --> 00:25:56.557 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've given him 30cc's of corophizine
to avoid secondary infection,

431
00:25:56.557 --> 00:25:58.787 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but so far, I've been unable
to lower his fever.

432
00:25:58.836 --> 00:26:00.555 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What are his chances?

433
00:26:02.336 --> 00:26:05.338 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Unless I find some way
to counteract the virus,

434
00:26:06.862 --> 00:26:07.607 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
he'll be dead in 12 hours.

435
00:26:08.730 --> 00:26:10.131 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Have you made any progress?

436
00:26:10.609 --> 00:26:11.810 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No.

437
00:26:12.409 --> 00:26:14.409 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've tried base pair destabilizers,

438
00:26:14.448 --> 00:26:17.290 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
sequential disruption--
nothing seems to affect it.

439
00:26:18.608 --> 00:26:21.890 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sir, I've got seven other aphasic patients

440
00:26:22.006 --> 00:26:24.525 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
displaying the same symptoms
as O'Brien here,

441
00:26:24.885 --> 00:26:26.426 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and I'm afraid this is only the beginning.

442
00:26:27.685 --> 00:26:29.484 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Keep searching, Doctor.

443
00:26:29.484 --> 00:26:33.297 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I hope Major Kira finds whoever's
responsible for creating this virus.

444
00:26:34.443 --> 00:26:35.904 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'd like to meet that person myself.

445
00:26:36.792 --> 00:26:38.562 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This virus is a work of genius.

446
00:26:39.210 --> 00:26:40.451 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll try to arrange it for you.

447
00:26:51.197 --> 00:26:53.797 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[womanr]<i> Link established with</i>
<i>the Bajoran Archival Records.</i>

448
00:26:54.562 --> 00:26:56.356 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Locate files on Velos VII Internment Camp.

449
00:26:56.436 --> 00:26:57.316 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female voice on computer]
<i>Ready.</i>

450
00:26:57.395 --> 00:27:00.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you show a record
of an inmate named Dekon Elig?

451
00:26:59.955 --> 00:27:01.354 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Affirmative.</i>

452
00:27:02.085 --> 00:27:03.255 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Biographical data.

453
00:27:04.214 --> 00:27:05.654 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Dekon Elig, geneticist.</i>

454
00:27:05.933 --> 00:27:09.256 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Former member of the Higa Metar sect</i>
<i>of the Bajoran underground.</i>

455
00:27:09.732 --> 00:27:12.492 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Killed while attempting escape,</i>
<i>Stardate 39355.</i>

456
00:27:13.931 --> 00:27:15.592 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Certificate of Death on file.</i>

457
00:27:17.171 --> 00:27:18.511 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No need to ask how you're doing.

458
00:27:18.769 --> 00:27:20.398 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Chasing after ghosts.

459
00:27:20.398 --> 00:27:21.904 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You have 12 hours to catch one.

460
00:27:22.499 --> 00:27:23.249 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And then?

461
00:27:23.908 --> 00:27:24.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
People start dying.

462
00:27:31.186 --> 00:27:32.305 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Computer...

463
00:27:35.144 --> 00:27:37.126 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
display Dekon Elig's Certificate of Death.

464
00:27:39.444 --> 00:27:40.804 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Identify signature of witness.

465
00:27:41.844 --> 00:27:44.723 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[woman]<i> Certificate of Death</i>
<i>was witnessed by Surmak Ren,</i>

466
00:27:44.802 --> 00:27:47.042 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Bajoran medical assistant.</i>

467
00:27:47.460 --> 00:27:49.942 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Show me biographical data on Surmak Ren.

468
00:27:50.779 --> 00:27:53.110 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Dr. Surmak Ren.</i>

469
00:27:53.110 --> 00:27:56.228 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Former member of the Higa Metar sect</i>
<i>of the Bajoran underground.</i>

470
00:27:56.358 --> 00:27:58.620 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Repatriated to Bajor upon closing</i>

471
00:27:58.517 --> 00:28:02.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>of the Velos VII Internment Camp,</i>
<i>Stardate 46302.</i>

472
00:28:03.154 --> 00:28:04.655 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Current status unknown.</i>

473
00:28:06.575 --> 00:28:09.414 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[clicking whir]

474
00:28:09.494 --> 00:28:11.653 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[clicking slows]

475
00:28:15.732 --> 00:28:16.932 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[clicking stops]

476
00:28:17.112 --> 00:28:18.292 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dabo.

477
00:28:24.529 --> 00:28:25.809 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Any luck?

478
00:28:26.887 --> 00:28:28.768 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I haven't won a spin in hours.

479
00:28:30.127 --> 00:28:31.888 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uh, care to place a friendly wager?

480
00:28:33.608 --> 00:28:35.589 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If it's your reputation
you're thinking about,

481
00:28:36.107 --> 00:28:37.087 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
no one need ever know.

482
00:28:37.176 --> 00:28:39.317 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It has nothing to do with my reputation.

483
00:28:40.004 --> 00:28:41.524 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

484
00:28:42.624 --> 00:28:44.154 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The truth is, I never...

485
00:28:46.283 --> 00:28:47.124 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
learned the game.

486
00:28:47.683 --> 00:28:49.384 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You mean, you've sat here
for all these years

487
00:28:49.384 --> 00:28:50.624 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and you don't even know how to gamble?

488
00:28:51.521 --> 00:28:52.282 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's correct.

489
00:28:53.481 --> 00:28:55.251 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No wonder you always look so bored.

490
00:28:56.940 --> 00:28:58.501 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The rules are quite simple, actually.

491
00:28:58.940 --> 00:29:01.139 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'd be happy to show them to you.

492
00:29:02.000 --> 00:29:03.440 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Some other time, perhaps.

493
00:29:03.750 --> 00:29:05.099 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sisko needs me in Ops.

494
00:29:05.818 --> 00:29:08.780 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And, since the entire security force
has been stricken with aphasia

495
00:29:09.476 --> 00:29:11.858 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the Promenade is in
a very vulnerable position.

496
00:29:12.715 --> 00:29:14.501 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How unfortunate.

497
00:29:15.635 --> 00:29:18.097 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Consider it a warning, Quark.

498
00:29:19.573 --> 00:29:22.455 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Because I'm holding you
personally responsible

499
00:29:22.455 --> 00:29:24.095 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
if anything turns up missing.

500
00:29:25.894 --> 00:29:27.253 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Is that understood?

501
00:29:28.291 --> 00:29:28.852 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Perfectly.

502
00:29:29.890 --> 00:29:30.929 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hmm.

503
00:29:40.011 --> 00:29:40.607 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dabo.

504
00:29:41.586 --> 00:29:44.768 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Computer, analyze test sample 37 delta.

505
00:29:45.126 --> 00:29:46.887 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Detail effects on viral containment.

506
00:29:47.325 --> 00:29:49.807 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female voice on computer]<i> Working.</i>
<i>Analysis complete.</i>

507
00:29:50.156 --> 00:29:52.226 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Sample 37 delta ineffective.</i>

508
00:29:53.324 --> 00:29:55.265 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Viral protein sheath is unaffected.</i>

509
00:29:55.582 --> 00:29:57.884 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Nucleotide sequence remains intact.</i>

510
00:30:00.201 --> 00:30:02.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Computer, replay morning.

511
00:30:03.320 --> 00:30:06.079 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female voice on computer]
<i>Command unclear. Please repeat.</i>

512
00:30:09.818 --> 00:30:12.620 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Glass lunch judge a bin to let it.

513
00:30:13.536 --> 00:30:16.216 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female voice on computer]
<i>Command unclear. Please repeat.</i>

514
00:30:28.269 --> 00:30:31.830 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Computer, establish a link
with the Bajoran Medical Index

515
00:30:31.850 --> 00:30:35.230 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
for the, uh, Northwestern District.

516
00:30:35.590 --> 00:30:36.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female voice on computer]
<i>Link established.</i>

517
00:30:37.030 --> 00:30:39.369 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Access all information on Dr. Surmak Ren.

518
00:30:39.930 --> 00:30:42.349 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female voice on computer]
<i>There are no records matching that name.</i>

519
00:30:43.030 --> 00:30:45.150 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Try the Northeastern District--
same search.

520
00:30:45.970 --> 00:30:48.230 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female voice on computer]
<i>Dr. Surmak Ren, currently serving</i>

521
00:30:48.250 --> 00:30:51.089 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>as Chief Administrator</i>
<i>of the Ilvian Medical Complex.</i>

522
00:30:51.769 --> 00:30:54.990 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Computer, open a channel
to the Ilvian Medical Complex

523
00:30:55.070 --> 00:30:56.349 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Administrator's office.

524
00:30:58.290 --> 00:31:00.809 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>This is Dr. Surmak. And you are?</i>

525
00:31:01.050 --> 00:31:04.589 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Major Kira Nerys,
Bajoran liaison to Deep Space 9.

526
00:31:04.830 --> 00:31:07.150 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Ah, yes, the old Cardassian</i>
<i>mining station.</i>

527
00:31:07.530 --> 00:31:08.650 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>How can I help you?</i>

528
00:31:08.890 --> 00:31:09.710 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It depends.

529
00:31:10.170 --> 00:31:10.809 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>On what?</i>

530
00:31:11.790 --> 00:31:13.830 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
On whether or not you helped Dekon Elig

531
00:31:13.850 --> 00:31:16.450 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
plant an aphasia virus here 18 years ago.

532
00:31:16.570 --> 00:31:18.230 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I have no idea what you're talking about.</i>

533
00:31:23.237 --> 00:31:25.538 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Look, Sisko, I'm a security officer--
a good one--

534
00:31:25.538 --> 00:31:28.218 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but that doesn't make me qualified
to help you run station operations.

535
00:31:28.218 --> 00:31:29.552 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're probably right, Constable.

536
00:31:29.389 --> 00:31:32.228 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But, as you can see,
you're all I've got.

537
00:31:32.308 --> 00:31:34.068 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Kira] Commander...

538
00:31:35.068 --> 00:31:38.266 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Commander, I think I found our scientist.

539
00:31:38.652 --> 00:31:40.053 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Does he have an antidote?
-I don't know.

540
00:31:40.053 --> 00:31:41.637 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He broke the connection
the minute I mentioned the virus.

541
00:31:41.741 --> 00:31:43.740 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Major, you mind telling me
where you're going?

542
00:31:44.233 --> 00:31:47.028 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
To continue my conversation
with Dr. Surmak, in person.

543
00:31:47.049 --> 00:31:49.368 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Major, I can't allow you
to break quarantine.

544
00:31:49.928 --> 00:31:51.328 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We can't risk
spreading the virus to Bajor.

545
00:31:51.647 --> 00:31:53.128 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am well aware of that, Commander.

546
00:31:53.128 --> 00:31:56.560 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
As a matter of fact,
I don't intend to step foot on the planet.

547
00:31:56.967 --> 00:31:58.727 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Better let her go, Sisko.

548
00:32:00.145 --> 00:32:01.026 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She's all we've got.

549
00:32:12.961 --> 00:32:15.943 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Let's just hope there's someone left
to greet her when she returns.

550
00:32:30.378 --> 00:32:31.476 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jake.

551
00:32:33.368 --> 00:32:34.554 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How's it going?

552
00:32:47.511 --> 00:32:50.179 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've missed you.

553
00:32:50.179 --> 00:32:51.900 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I know things don't look
too good right now,

554
00:32:52.929 --> 00:32:54.189 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but they'll get better.

555
00:32:55.488 --> 00:32:56.549 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You have to believe that...

556
00:32:58.688 --> 00:33:01.207 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
because I'm not going
to lose you, Jake.

557
00:33:02.207 --> 00:33:02.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You hear me?

558
00:33:04.285 --> 00:33:06.285 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm not going to lose you.

559
00:33:21.306 --> 00:33:22.247 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You better take a look at this.

560
00:33:22.260 --> 00:33:24.020 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We have activity on Docking Port 5.

561
00:33:24.099 --> 00:33:25.539 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think a ship is about to depart.

562
00:33:25.619 --> 00:33:27.459 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Docking Port 5? That's Jaheel's ship.

563
00:33:27.798 --> 00:33:29.102 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Put him on screen.

564
00:33:34.377 --> 00:33:37.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain, your ship has
not been cleared for departure.

565
00:33:37.496 --> 00:33:38.797 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The mooring clamps are locked,

566
00:33:38.896 --> 00:33:40.137 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and I don't intend to release them.

567
00:33:41.195 --> 00:33:43.117 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I suggest you change your mind.</i>

568
00:33:43.515 --> 00:33:45.656 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I'm taking aft thrusters to one half.</i>

569
00:33:48.993 --> 00:33:51.815 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain, cut your engines
before you rip your ship apart.

570
00:33:53.584 --> 00:33:54.790 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's not reducing power.

571
00:33:55.703 --> 00:33:57.946 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jaheel, I'm ordering you to stand down.

572
00:33:58.508 --> 00:34:00.588 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Your orders are no concern of mine.</i>

573
00:34:00.666 --> 00:34:03.527 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>My entire crew has been</i>
<i>confined to your hospital.</i>

574
00:34:03.547 --> 00:34:06.346 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I must leave now</i>
<i>while I can still function.</i>

575
00:34:06.583 --> 00:34:10.026 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Look, I understand that you're frightened
but believe me, you're better off here.

576
00:34:10.635 --> 00:34:12.857 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You don't want to be out there alone
and get hit by the virus.

577
00:34:12.805 --> 00:34:15.324 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Don't worry about me, I'm fine.</i>

578
00:34:16.404 --> 00:34:18.923 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>And I plan to stay that way.</i>

579
00:34:19.212 --> 00:34:20.923 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-And if you think you're go--
-[cuts transmission]

580
00:34:22.982 --> 00:34:24.243 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We'll have to retract the clamps.

581
00:34:24.382 --> 00:34:28.300 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Once he's clear of the station
we can grab him with a tractor beam.

582
00:34:34.578 --> 00:34:36.138 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Damn.
-What's wrong?

583
00:34:36.718 --> 00:34:38.379 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There's too much stress
on the mooring clamps.

584
00:34:38.517 --> 00:34:39.837 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They're not retracting.

585
00:34:40.397 --> 00:34:42.557 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groaning]

586
00:34:42.716 --> 00:34:45.035 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[console beeping]

587
00:34:45.676 --> 00:34:47.995 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
His aft isolation plate buckled.

588
00:34:48.716 --> 00:34:50.394 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
His main power core's been ruptured.

589
00:34:51.035 --> 00:34:53.874 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If the internal fuel cells collapse,
the whole ship will explode.

590
00:34:53.954 --> 00:34:56.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And take half the docking ring with it.

591
00:35:06.750 --> 00:35:08.862 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Computer, isolate a com line

592
00:35:08.862 --> 00:35:11.507 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to the Ilvian Medical Complex
Administrator's office.

593
00:35:11.769 --> 00:35:12.869 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[female voice on computer]<i> Line isolated.</i>

594
00:35:13.547 --> 00:35:14.988 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Scan office for life-forms.

595
00:35:15.466 --> 00:35:17.506 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>One life-form present.</i>

596
00:35:17.986 --> 00:35:19.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Lock on and stand by to transport.

597
00:35:22.824 --> 00:35:25.423 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>-This is Dr. Surmak.</i>
-Hello again, Doctor.

598
00:35:25.504 --> 00:35:27.560 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just checking to see
you're in your office.

599
00:35:27.823 --> 00:35:29.223 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I have nothing to say to you--</i>

600
00:35:36.740 --> 00:35:38.459 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hello again, Doctor.

601
00:35:38.839 --> 00:35:40.159 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is outrageous.

602
00:35:40.980 --> 00:35:43.061 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I demand you return me
to my office immediately.

603
00:35:43.178 --> 00:35:45.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Relax, Doctor. You won't be gone long.

604
00:35:51.136 --> 00:35:53.438 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Try to reestablish visual contact
with Jaheel's ship.

605
00:35:56.520 --> 00:35:57.894 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Odo] No response. His com lines are down.

606
00:35:58.093 --> 00:36:00.773 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Bypass communications
through a secondary grid.

607
00:36:01.300 --> 00:36:03.001 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
See if you can switch
to external pickups.

608
00:36:03.452 --> 00:36:04.371 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Got it.

609
00:36:07.630 --> 00:36:10.072 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
His fire control systems
don't appear to be working.

610
00:36:11.711 --> 00:36:14.592 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We have about 15 minutes
before the fuel cells collapse.

611
00:36:16.308 --> 00:36:17.929 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I hope you feel better than you look.

612
00:36:19.228 --> 00:36:20.588 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Must be that damn virus.

613
00:36:21.787 --> 00:36:23.347 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is Sisko.

614
00:36:23.786 --> 00:36:26.969 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Any station personnel who can understand
what I'm saying, come to Ops immediately.

615
00:36:26.969 --> 00:36:27.847 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We need help up here.

616
00:36:28.528 --> 00:36:30.648 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We have to get that ship
away from the station.

617
00:36:31.144 --> 00:36:32.806 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why don't we explode
the mooring clamps?

618
00:36:33.063 --> 00:36:35.325 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The blast should push the ship
away from the docking ring.

619
00:36:35.662 --> 00:36:37.742 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We'll have to get down there
and blow it manually.

620
00:36:38.101 --> 00:36:39.461 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groans]

621
00:36:39.461 --> 00:36:40.521 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll do it.

622
00:36:41.821 --> 00:36:42.860 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right.

623
00:36:43.720 --> 00:36:44.901 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You can cross barrels.

624
00:36:46.160 --> 00:36:47.719 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All job appalled.

625
00:36:48.679 --> 00:36:49.259 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What was that?

626
00:36:51.257 --> 00:36:51.658 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Bread...

627
00:36:52.699 --> 00:36:53.399 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
the arrive...

628
00:36:54.198 --> 00:36:55.378 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
seen earlier.

629
00:36:57.837 --> 00:36:59.996 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, I see.

630
00:37:08.793 --> 00:37:10.652 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Major, this is kidnapping.

631
00:37:11.184 --> 00:37:12.478 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Turn this ship around
or I swear you will spend

632
00:37:12.478 --> 00:37:14.807 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the rest of your life
in Kran-Tobol Prison.

633
00:37:15.030 --> 00:37:17.732 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Fine. But first, we need your help.

634
00:37:18.904 --> 00:37:20.657 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The aphasia virus is spreading
through the station.

635
00:37:21.310 --> 00:37:22.090 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why come to me?

636
00:37:22.669 --> 00:37:24.310 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You helped create the virus, didn't you?

637
00:37:24.688 --> 00:37:26.330 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No, I had practically
nothing to do with it.

638
00:37:27.089 --> 00:37:28.469 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dekon Elig created the virus.

639
00:37:29.008 --> 00:37:30.848 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I was merely his medical assistant.

640
00:37:31.168 --> 00:37:33.087 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That seems like a lifetime ago now.

641
00:37:33.206 --> 00:37:35.007 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was only in the underground
for six months

642
00:37:35.007 --> 00:37:36.047 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
before we were captured.

643
00:37:36.786 --> 00:37:38.387 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am not responsible for this.

644
00:37:38.444 --> 00:37:40.025 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am not looking to place blame!

645
00:37:40.203 --> 00:37:42.025 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All I want is the antidote.

646
00:37:43.163 --> 00:37:44.423 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't know of any antidote.

647
00:37:45.163 --> 00:37:46.804 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If Dekon created one, he never told me.

648
00:37:47.320 --> 00:37:47.801 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Listen, Surmak.

649
00:37:49.001 --> 00:37:50.662 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I have a station full of dying people

650
00:37:50.941 --> 00:37:54.403 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and you are the closest thing there is
to an expert on this virus.

651
00:37:54.940 --> 00:37:56.110 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I sympathize, Major,

652
00:37:56.318 --> 00:37:57.919 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but I don't think I can help you.

653
00:37:59.197 --> 00:38:00.690 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right.

654
00:38:01.977 --> 00:38:03.537 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then how about helping yourself?

655
00:38:04.497 --> 00:38:05.617 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Meaning what?

656
00:38:06.136 --> 00:38:07.176 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Meaning...

657
00:38:08.815 --> 00:38:11.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've been infected
with your virus, Doctor...

658
00:38:13.215 --> 00:38:14.876 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
so now you're infected, too.

659
00:38:20.572 --> 00:38:22.713 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
To anyone who can hear me, this is Odo.

660
00:38:23.581 --> 00:38:24.331 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sisko's infected.

661
00:38:24.331 --> 00:38:25.849 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I could really use some help here in Ops.

662
00:38:25.870 --> 00:38:29.348 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do I detect a note of panic in your voice?

663
00:38:29.429 --> 00:38:30.547 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Quark.

664
00:38:31.889 --> 00:38:34.710 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Am I to believe that you're
volunteering to help?

665
00:38:35.128 --> 00:38:37.249 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Who said anything about volunteering?

666
00:38:37.470 --> 00:38:39.111 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We can haggle over price later.

667
00:38:39.365 --> 00:38:40.565 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now, um...

668
00:38:41.164 --> 00:38:43.484 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
how may I be of use?

669
00:38:44.585 --> 00:38:46.426 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I need to get to Docking Port 5 now.

670
00:38:46.663 --> 00:38:48.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That ship's going to explode
in five minutes.

671
00:38:49.939 --> 00:38:50.582 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll beam you over.

672
00:38:50.882 --> 00:38:52.563 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-You?
-Relax.

673
00:38:53.142 --> 00:38:55.903 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I served on a Ferengi freighter
for eight years.

674
00:38:57.901 --> 00:38:59.180 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right.

675
00:38:59.921 --> 00:39:02.843 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I must have witnessed the procedure
hundreds of times.

676
00:39:03.018 --> 00:39:06.080 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Witnessed? You mean to say you never
handled the controls yourself?

677
00:39:06.778 --> 00:39:08.057 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Energizing!

678
00:39:15.384 --> 00:39:16.654 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighing]

679
00:39:26.092 --> 00:39:28.651 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Kira to Ops. Approaching Landing Pad 7.

680
00:39:28.730 --> 00:39:30.970 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Request clearance
to initiate docking procedure.

681
00:39:31.049 --> 00:39:33.729 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Quark]<i> Welcome back.</i>
<i>I could use some help up here.</i>

682
00:39:33.809 --> 00:39:36.788 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Quark, what are you doing in Ops?

683
00:39:36.808 --> 00:39:38.715 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughing]

684
00:39:42.687 --> 00:39:43.647 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
First thing I need to see

685
00:39:43.647 --> 00:39:45.758 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
is your doctor's viral
characterization research.

686
00:39:49.945 --> 00:39:51.847 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He was beginning to develop
an antidote series.

687
00:39:51.847 --> 00:39:52.845 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let's take a look at that.

688
00:39:53.628 --> 00:39:55.047 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Kira] Listen, Doctor, um...

689
00:39:55.126 --> 00:39:56.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll be in Ops.

690
00:39:56.182 --> 00:39:57.924 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If you need me, use this string impact.

691
00:39:59.381 --> 00:40:01.141 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Lot show red intense.

692
00:40:02.882 --> 00:40:04.263 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think you'd better sit down, Major.

693
00:40:09.239 --> 00:40:11.678 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[alarm wailing]

694
00:40:23.875 --> 00:40:26.595 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Jaheel] Dog fellow distance.

695
00:40:26.674 --> 00:40:28.194 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Odo] Yeah, tell me about it.

696
00:40:28.194 --> 00:40:29.644 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Quark]<i> Odo, you'd better hurry up.</i>

697
00:40:30.274 --> 00:40:32.433 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That ship's going to explode
in one minute.

698
00:40:35.752 --> 00:40:37.353 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Virum protein sheath.

699
00:40:38.121 --> 00:40:39.411 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nucleotide sequence.

700
00:40:40.680 --> 00:40:41.640 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes.

701
00:40:41.720 --> 00:40:42.759 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's right.

702
00:40:42.840 --> 00:40:44.999 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's an adaptive, synaptic inhibitor.

703
00:40:45.730 --> 00:40:46.749 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dekon was brilliant.

704
00:40:46.967 --> 00:40:47.728 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No doubt of that.

705
00:40:49.028 --> 00:40:51.516 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think we've found your antidote, Major.

706
00:40:54.906 --> 00:40:56.546 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Quark]<i> 40 seconds.</i>

707
00:41:09.341 --> 00:41:10.661 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
30 seconds. Hurry!

708
00:41:10.981 --> 00:41:12.620 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I know, I know.

709
00:41:17.099 --> 00:41:18.899 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
20 seconds!

710
00:41:24.377 --> 00:41:26.216 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ten seconds!

711
00:41:26.297 --> 00:41:28.056 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[alarm blares]

712
00:41:28.136 --> 00:41:29.016 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasps]

713
00:41:50.209 --> 00:41:52.009 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Quark]<i> Odo? Quark to Odo.</i>

714
00:41:52.009 --> 00:41:52.629 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You still with us?

715
00:41:53.588 --> 00:41:55.569 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Try not to sound too disappointed.

716
00:41:56.027 --> 00:41:58.948 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, about that little matter
of my hazard pay...

717
00:41:59.946 --> 00:42:01.626 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why, you...

718
00:42:05.664 --> 00:42:07.663 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come on. Come on.

719
00:42:11.456 --> 00:42:14.025 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Sisko]<i> Station Log, Stardate 46425.8.</i>

720
00:42:15.200 --> 00:42:16.821 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>With the help of Dr. Bashir's notes,</i>

721
00:42:17.021 --> 00:42:20.063 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Dr. Surmak was able to find</i>
<i>an antidote for the aphasia virus.</i>

722
00:42:20.480 --> 00:42:22.981 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We are continuing to administer</i>
<i>it throughout the station</i>

723
00:42:23.299 --> 00:42:25.121 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>and things are slowly</i>
<i>returning to normal.</i>

724
00:42:25.977 --> 00:42:27.497 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Good to have you back, Chief.

725
00:42:27.577 --> 00:42:28.976 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you, sir.

726
00:42:29.057 --> 00:42:30.297 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Coffee, black.

727
00:42:37.134 --> 00:42:38.174 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
O'Brien!

